The Closet;;78;;85;;R;;When Francois Pignon (Daniel Auteuil), an accountant for a rubber factory, is about to be fired, he spreads a rumor that he's gay so that the company will be afraid to fire him, lest they come under fire for sexual discrimination. The ruse quickly becomes a challenge, starting when a burly homophobe (Gérard Depardieu) befriends Pignon to also keep his own job for the opposite reason.;;Comedy;;Francis Veber;;2001;;Daniel Auteuil,Gérard Depardieu,Thierry Lhermitte,Michèle Laroque,Michel Aumont;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/closet